- **Wood**: Pycnoxylic. Tracheids only (no vessels). Resin canals. Narrow rays.
- **Phloem**: Sieve cells (no sieve tubes).
- **Shoots**: Long shoots (scale leaves) and short shoots (needle leaves) in pines.

#figure(
  image(images.at("22-15").path, width: 50%),
  caption: [#images.at("22-15").caption]
)

#figure(
  image(images.at("22-16").path, width: 50%),
  caption: [#images.at("22-16").caption]
)

- **Reproduction**:
  - **Pollen Cones**: Simple cones. Axis with microsporophylls.
    - Microspores develop into pollen grains (4 cells: 2 prothallial, 1 generative, 1 tube).
    - Air bladders for buoyancy.
  - **Seed Cones**: Compound cones. Axis with cone bracts. Axillary buds modified into ovuliferous scales (fused megasporophylls).
    - Megaspore retained. Develops into coenocytic megagametophyte.
    - Archegonia form with large eggs.
  - **Fertilization**: Pollen tube digests way to egg (siphonogamy). Non-motile sperm.
  - **Embryogeny**: Suspensor pushes proembryo into megagametophyte (nutritive tissue). Polyembryony common (only one survives).
  - **Seed**: Seed coat (integument), embryo, megagametophyte (food).

